383,IssuesEvent,2018-05-19 06:28:17+00:00,20857415,Kuniwak/vint,1124024,Kuniwak,,,closed,ProhibitImplicitScopeVariable is not an anitpattern,"[{'id': 721986779, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Kuniwak/vint/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': '61ddbc', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'Kuniwak', 'id': 1124024, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1124024?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/Kuniwak', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Kuniwak/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",18,"In my opinion, and probably in most people's opinion, this should not be considered an antipattern or be enabled by default. Most plugin authors prefer to use implicit scope, at least for local variables inside functions. When scope is specified everywhere, the code inside functions becomes less readable. It also trains the reader to ignore the scope, thereby not noticing when a special scope is used.

Even inside one's main config file, it would be strange and unnecessary to specify global scope for every variable you set outside of a function.

The default scope rules when you don't specify the scope are very appropriate, global when outside a function, and local when inside a function.",{},{}
