727,IssuesEvent,2017-10-24 04:30:52+00:00,14900247,skoczen/will,200635,skoczen,,,closed,Plugin.say room parameter not user friendly,[],[],2,"It didn't make sense to me how in configs we refer to rooms as strings but in `say` we need a `Room` object. The `Room` object isn't defined in the docs so the user would have to figure out how `Plugin` populates `self._available_rooms` to figure out everything works.

I propose we change the parameter to accept a room string, so going from

`self.say('the time is {} '.format(datetime.datetime.now()), room=self.available_rooms['CHEF'])`

to

`self.say('the time is {} '.format(datetime.datetime.now()), room='CHEF')`

If backwards compatibility is a big issue, we could do a typecheck to still support passing a Room object.

The code change would be simple and I'd be happy to submit a pull request.",{},{}
