1152,IssuesEvent,2015-04-05 06:19:19+00:00,28530868,cannatag/ldap3,1319333,cannatag,,,closed,"Attempts to connect to an LDAP server fail with ""LDAPSocketOpenError: invalid server address"" on FreeBSD",[],[],3,"Any attempt to connect to an LDAP server fails with ""LDAPSocketOpenError: invalid server address"" on FreeBSD. This is because getaddrinfo(3) on FreeBSD does not accept AI_V4MAPPED flag as a hint, and fails with error code 3 (""Invalid value for ai_flags"") if this flag is set. The following patch fixed (or worked around) the problem for me: https://gist.github.com/andriy-s/ac502e1d27ba4f19912d",{},{}
