1808,IssuesEvent,2018-05-18 10:51:05+00:00,11380094,msiemens/tinydb,26384082,stale[bot],,,closed,A function that updates entries in the db and does not produce duplicates.,"[{'id': 664666354, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/msiemens/tinydb/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}, {'id': 801483870, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/msiemens/tinydb/labels/stale', 'name': 'stale', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': False}]",[],6,"At the moment I want to create a small database with <10000 entries and <10 different keys. I found tinydb as I am coding a lot in Python and I did not want to learn SQL etc. 
There is one major function missing that does the following. 

Using letters  for keys and integers as values. Assume the db has the entries:
```
1: {A:1} 
2: {B:2, C:42}
3: {A:3, C:42}
```
Now you want to insert `{A:1, B:2, C:42}` and the db should look like this: 
```
1: {A:1, B:2, C:42} 
3: {A:3, C:42}
```

What happened? 

1.  `{A:1}` was updated to `{A:1,B:2,C:42}`.
2.  `{B:2, C:42}` was updated to `{A:1,B:2,C:42}`. This entry got removed as it is now a duplicate.
3.  `{A:3;C:42}`  has been untouched


I am looking for advise, as this kind of update method get's awfully slow and there might be an elegant way that I don't see.  
Has anyone ever coded such a function?
Is there a method that cleans the database from duplicates? 

I have created two methods that I can share, if desired. One is unusable due to runtime ^^, but the other one works ""ok"". 

Thx for your help. ",{},{}
