1940,IssuesEvent,2015-01-15 08:43:43+00:00,17214270,xlcnd/isbntools,6782145,xlcnd,,,closed,`isbn_meta` doesn't work with output redirection (for some ISBNs),"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/xlcnd/isbntools/labels/info', 'name': 'info', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],2,"The culprit of this error is the 'infamous' `UnicodeEncodeError: 'ascii' codec can't encode character` error of python 2. This should not be a problem with python 3 however...

Python 2 `print` function, overcomes this problem only when the output is a terminal, not when is a file.

Unfortunately the solution is not so simple and I suggest that, if you need to redirect the output, you use python 3 OR do your own script using `isbntools.meta` function and with the help of the `codecs` module you write the information to a file.

Thanks to Michael Metze for make me aware of this issue.",{},{}
