2341,IssuesEvent,2016-11-30 19:02:50+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,1350280,jimfunk,,,opened,flush_routes leaking memory,[],[],0,"I noticed an issue running on a system with full table BGP where calling flush_routes on a separate routing table takes a long time and consumes nearly 6G of RAM which is never released.

Here's a quick way to replicate:

```
pip install pyasn
pyasn_util_download.py --latest
pyasn_util_convert.py --single rib.20161128.2200.bz2 theinternet  # Adjust for the file it downloaded
gateway=$(ip r show exact 0.0.0.0/0 | cut -d "" "" -f 3)
interface=$(ip r show exact 0.0.0.0/0 | cut -d "" "" -f 5)
while read prefix ; do ip r add $prefix via $gateway dev $interface ; done < <(awk '{print $1}' < /usr/src/bi/theinternet)
python3 -c 'import pyroute2; pyroute2.IPRoute().flush_routes(table=1000)'
```",{},{}
