2531,IssuesEvent,2016-02-15 18:04:08+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,843444,dpkp,,,closed,Help: KafkaClient in client_async.py fails in python3,[],[],3,"I'm running python 3.4.2 with Kafka 0.8.1.1

I've had a quick look and submitted a (broken) PR.

Issue looks to be that ConnectionError isn't defined in PY3:

At line 23 if `kafka.client_async`, `six.PY2 == True` defines `ConnectionError = None` but six.PY3 will not assign it to anything. The assertion checking for the exception type at line 628 will then fail.

The follow snippet demonstrates this under 3.4.2:

```
>>> import six
>>> if six.PY2:
...     ConnectionError = None
... 
>>> f = IOError
>>> assert isinstance(f, ConnectionError)
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
AssertionError
```",{},{}
