3186,IssuesEvent,2018-02-15 07:17:40+00:00,55371899,rbarrois/aionotify,187641,riccardodivirgilio,,,opened,Max OSX 10.13.2 cannot find libc.so.6 ,[],[],0,"this is happening because the default location is different.
inotify module is using a different code:
https://github.com/dsoprea/PyInotify/blob/master/inotify/library.py

instead of hardcoding 'libc.so.6' is using ctypes.util.find_library, so basically to fix this issue it looks like you can just use this on line 15:

https://github.com/rbarrois/aionotify/blob/master/aionotify/base.py
_libc = ctypes.cdll.LoadLibrary(ctypes.util.find_library('c') or 'libc.so.6')

this fix seems to work.
can I create a pull request?

thanks
",{},{}
