5064,IssuesEvent,2016-02-01 14:01:17+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,closed,Smart Iteration with reverse()'d queryset has a broken report,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/adamchainz/django-mysql/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/adamchainz/django-mysql/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': 'eb6420'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/adamchainz/django-mysql/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818'}]",[],1,"When using a queryset with `.reverse()` applied and `report_progress=True`, you get a report that ends:

`highest pk so far 1234`

The number at the end keeps falling, and the re-writing process (writing `\r` then rewriting the string) then screws up when you drop one decimal place, for example when you hit the pk 999 the report actually reads:

`highest pk so far 9994`

Because that `4` is not erased. If we could write out as many spaces as required to the end of the line, *then* `\r`, it should always work to erase the text.

N.B. I'm not sure how this interacts with terminals that wrap lines, or resizing, etc.",{},{}
