[url()’s support for inline flags in regular expression groups ((?i), (?L), (?m), (?s), and (?u)) is removed.](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/2.1/releases/2.1/)

bootstrap_pagination.py line 85 url += '?' + url_get_params.urlencode() calls to django/http/request.py and gives an error: ""'int' object has no attribute encode"".
