7319,IssuesEvent,2015-10-20 23:14:28+00:00,6930489,facebook/watchman,1010987,bmdhacks,69631,facebook,opened,Dangling symlinks missed in OSX,[],[],0,"This is an OSX bug, but I figured I'd fill you guys in because it's causing Twitter all kinds of headaches.  Here's a repro:

    #!/usr/bin/env bash
    
    set -x
    
    watchman watch .
    watchman since . n:foo
    ls -lh path0sym
    mkdir path2 path3 path3/subp3
    paths=""path0 path2/file2 path3/file3 path3/subp3/file3""
    (
      for p in $paths
    	do
    		echo ""hello $p"" >$p || exit 1
    		ln -s ""hello $p"" ${p}sym || exit 1
    	done
    )
    ls -lh path0sym
   watchman since . n:foo

Note that the second 'since' query doesn't return any of the *sym files that were created.  Change `""hello $p""` to `""$(basename $p)""` and it will work.

",{},{}
