7745,IssuesEvent,2017-10-10 08:30:15+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,4190164,zhenlineo,201120,neo4j,closed,acquireWriteLock,[],[],3,"Hi,

I am trying to use Tracastions in a multi-processing environment. However, at the moment if any 2 processes want to commit at the same time, they one of them will error out as there is a lock in place.

I see that in the Java driver, one can check for a lock with tx.acquireWriteLock(). This would be a good way to conditionally commit transactions in different processors.

Is there an equivalent in the Python driver?

Vlad",{},{}
