8512,IssuesEvent,2017-11-07 20:06:11+00:00,2625205,robotframework/SeleniumLibrary,2665023,aaltat,574284,robotframework,closed,`Set Screenshot Directory` is inconsistent with other `Set ...` keywords,"[{'id': 205419975, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/SeleniumLibrary/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 496537198, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/SeleniumLibrary/labels/bwic', 'name': 'bwic', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 679743440, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/SeleniumLibrary/labels/prio-low', 'name': 'prio-low', 'color': '41ae76', 'default': False}, {'id': 679743363, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/SeleniumLibrary/labels/rc%201', 'name': 'rc 1', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Keywords that set configuration values like `Set Selenium Timeout` and `Set Selenium Implicit Wait` simply change the value in library and return the old value to allow restoring it later if needed. `Set Screenshot Directory` works differently and instead tries to restore the old value automatically. This is problematic for various reasons:

- This behavior is inconsistent with other `Set ...` keywords.
- How restoring actually works isn't adequately documented.
- There seem to be bugs related to this. I started getting error `[ ERROR ] Calling method 'end_test' of listener 'LibraryListener' failed: IndexError: pop from empty list` from this code in some SL tests.

Automatically restoring the original value might be a good feature, but it should be used consistently, be documented better, and obviously also fixed. All that is way too much work, and instead we'll remove this functionality from `Set Screenshot Directory` and change it to work as other `Set ...` keywords.
",{},{}
