9345,IssuesEvent,2015-04-22 18:37:06+00:00,2562442,mozilla-services/cornice,686587,aguereca,1066228,mozilla-services,closed,1.0.0 Broke resource routing,[],[],4,"Asume a file `my_views.py`

``` python
from cornice.resource import resource, view

@resource(collection_path='/user/{id}/follow', path='/user/{id}/follow')
class UserFollowViews(object):
    ...
    @view(validators=(validate_authentication, validate_user))
    def post(self):
    ....


@resource(collection_path='/user/{id}/following', path='/user/{id}/following')
class UserFollowingViews(object):
    ...
    @view(validators=(validate_authentication, validate_user))
    def collection_get(self):
    ....
```

With 1.0.0 , using proutes I can see broken routes and all requests accessing them will return 404 Not Found:

Name                    |      Pattern                  |    Method   |   View       
------------------------|-----------------------------|---------------|---------
userfollowviews |  /user/{id}/follow | POST   |  my_views.UserFollowViews.post__POST
userfollowingviews | /user/{id}/following  |   *  |  `<unknown>`

I had to downgrade and fix versions to 0.20.0 to solve this.

After a quick look into the commits of 1.0.0 and can't single on a commit that might cause this, a more experienced eye on the routing internals could be of help here.",{},{}
