9546,IssuesEvent,2015-01-28 21:28:23+00:00,8146436,zopefoundation/zope.i18n,242750,tseaver,1163184,zopefoundation,opened,No way to format percentages including decimals in `nl` locale,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zopefoundation/zope.i18n/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"In https://bugs.launchpad.net/zope.i18n/+bug/686058, @wichert reported:

> In the nl locale percentages are always formatted without decimals:

```python
>>> locale.numbers.getFormatter(""percent"").format(50.1)
'50%'
```

> For most other things a locale can format you can use a 'long' length to get more information. No such luck here though:

```python
>>> locale.numbers.getFormatter(""percent"", length=""long"").format(50.1)
KeyError: ('long',)
```",{},{}
