9697,IssuesEvent,2018-05-07 14:04:31+00:00,2866041,kivy/python-for-android,1265819,inclement,1266152,kivy,closed,Use travis to automatically test builds on different platforms,[],[],9,"@kived:

> Do you mean use Travis to check for these issues? My primary concern there would be the build time required to check everything. Maybe if it could be set up to run once a night rather than whenever a commit happens - won't get immediate results, but issues would still be detected. But mostly I think the revamp just hasn't been tested well in OSX, not that there is any regression.

Yeah I meant to setup travis to continuously check for build issues. We can use something like [nightli.es](https://nightli.es) for this. Or any alternative mentioned [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20395624/travis-ci-builds-on-schedule).
