10059,IssuesEvent,2018-03-06 23:04:48+00:00,25181584,h2oai/sparkling-water,3013418,Tagar,1402695,h2oai,opened,OOM - workarounds for widedatasets,[],[],0,"We have a 130Gb parquet table trying to build a simple GLM model and getting OOMs.
40 executors x 17Gb spark.executor.memory each = 680Gb.
Would you recommend some fine tuning for this (larger) dataset? 
There are 63m records x 6300 columns in this dataset.
Is there is something special would you recommend for this larger dataset?

Also, would you recommend some particular settings for ```spark.memory.fraction``` and ```spark.memory.storageFraction```? I think we should set at least ```spark.memory.storageFraction``` to a much lower value as we don't use Spark caching when we run Sparkling Water - data is in-memoried with h2o frames. Similarly, ```spark.memory.fraction``` should be lowered so more memory is available for H2O which lives in the same JVMs as Spark executors.

