10663,IssuesEvent,2017-04-20 17:01:20+00:00,4333252,Guake/guake,133498,Stibbons,1741188,Guake,closed,Quick Open does not work with dashes,[],[],10,"If there is a `-` in the filename or path, guake does not recognize the string as a file.  For example:

``` bash
$ touch /home/user/test.txt:1
$ echo /home/user/test.txt:1
/home/user/test.txt:1
$ # ^ This will be underlined and opens on ctrl+click

$ touch /home/user/test-file.txt:1
$ echo /home/user/test-file.txt:1
/home/user/test-file.txt:1
$ # ^ This is not recognized as a file, no underline, no opening.
```
",{},{}
