11587,IssuesEvent,2017-04-05 00:55:50+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,6178947,JasonQSong,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Nodejs should inject environment PATH when installing a binary,[],[],0,"https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/contrib/node/src/python/pants/contrib/node/subsystems/node_distribution.py#L109

Nodejs must inject environment PATH when installing it. A lot of node modules have scripts that invoke environment nodejs distribution directly. Currently, the PATH injection happens when the command is being invoked. For different nodejs command, it's injecting different PATH. This bug didn't appear when there are only two nodejs commands (node, npm) are running because node and npm are sharing the same bin directory. Now, since yarnpkg is installed in a separate directory with a different package, the injection should happen whenever binary is being installed.",{},{}
11589,IssuesEvent,2018-04-26 19:30:16+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Function to merge two Snapshot values,[],"[{'login': 'stuhood', 'id': 46740, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/46740?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/stuhood', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/stuhood/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",4,"The [Snapshot type](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/e20b205fa8d065222c03f47b16187a65ddf60efa/src/rust/engine/fs/src/snapshot.rs#L28-L31) represents a set of files, which have particular contents.

In order to merge snapshots (e.g. ""a snapshot containing a compiler binary"" and ""some source files to compile"") for process execution, we need to be able to merge snapshots.

Exactly how we expose this in Python is an open question (https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/issues/5502) but it's reasonable to assume we'll want an in-rust implementation of merging which we expose to the Python _somehow_. So, let's write a static function (and some tests!) in snapshot.rs.

Snapshots have two components, which will need handling separately:
1. Digest. This is the digest the [Directory protocol buffer](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/e20b205fa8d065222c03f47b16187a65ddf60efa/3rdparty/protobuf/googleapis/google/devtools/remoteexecution/v1test/remote_execution.proto#L431-L497) which represents the tree of files. Note that there are strict ordering requirements (alphabetical) for entries in this.

2. path_stats. This is a list of the entries in the Snapshot, ordered in the order that they were captured (i.e. grabbing a snapshot for `[""foo"", ""bar""]` will have its `path_stats` in that order). There isn't necessarily an obviously correct ordering here, so we should probably preserve the ordering of the first snapshot passed, and insert additional `PathStats` in a stable order afterwards (deduplicating as we go).",{},{}
