11642,IssuesEvent,2018-05-14 20:37:22+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,28027359,dotordogh,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Cache key for python_binary doesn't include platforms when passed as option,[],[],0,"When creating two python binaries that are compatible with different sets of platforms, the cache must be cleared between the creation of the two binaries. Steps to repro:

With the following target:
```
python_binary(
  name='pants_platforms',
  entry_point=''',
  dependencies = [
    '3rdparty/python:numpy'
  ]
)
```
Run the following sequence (on OSX):
```
$ ./pants clean-all
$ rm -rf ~/.cache/pants/
$ ./pants binary pants_platforms --python-setup-platforms='[""linux-x86_64""]'
# pex found in ./dist contains only linux compatible libraries
$ ./pants binary pants_platforms --python-setup-platforms='[""linux-x86_64"", ""current""]'
# pex found in ./dist should contain ""current"" platform compatible libs and linux but only contains linux libs 
```
If you clear the cache at `~/.cache/pants` between the two runs then it behaves as expected. ",{},{}
