12280,IssuesEvent,2016-04-20 15:57:00+00:00,10247874,docker/docker-py,627127,Gnork,5429470,docker,closed,Feature request: set Swarm filter constraint on container create,[],[],0,"With Docker Swarm it is possible to set filter constraints, in order to select a Swarm Agent with certain properties. With the CLI tool this can be accomplished by specifying the ""-e"" parameter as described in the [official documentation:](https://docs.docker.com/swarm/scheduler/filter/)

In the following example the node is selected by its name (agent1):
`docker run -it --rm -e constraint:node==agent1 ubuntu:trusty /bin/bash`

Maybe this is already possible with docker-py, but I couldn't figure it out.

Christoph",{},{}
