12463,IssuesEvent,2016-05-11 16:53:00+00:00,13415322,python-xmp-toolkit/python-xmp-toolkit,5863446,MaxyMoos,5638728,python-xmp-toolkit,opened,restype = check_error causes problems on Windows environments,[],[],0,"Hello,

I am currently porting a Python program using libxmp onto Windows 7 and I noticed that I got caught in an infinite loop that doesn't happen on my Linux environment (Ubuntu 14.04):

Using `get_array_item` to walk through a sequence is the culprit, and peculiarly the `check_error` call through the ctypes `restype` variable:
I dumped the value of the `success` parameter while executing the program and it seems like on a Windows environment, when `xmp_get_array_item` returns True, we get success = 1, but when `xmp_get_array_item` returns False, we get... something that is not 1 (various high int values), so the loop of `XMPMeta.count_array_items` goes on indefinitely.

I suspect this is due to the internals of ctypes and ctypes.WinDLL, but the solution I've implemented for now is the following one: replace the `restype = check_error` assignation by `restype = ctypes.c_bool `and call the check_error function on the return value of xmp_get_array_item.

I've only done it for this function in my code, but it might be worth doing this kind of fix in the whole lib in order to enhance Windows compatibility.
Anyway it's up to you guys to decide if you think that's worth it !

Workaround code:
```
def get_array_item(xmp, schema, name, index):
    EXEMPI.xmp_get_array_item.restype = ctypes.c_bool
    EXEMPI.xmp_get_array_item.argtypes = [ctypes.c_void_p,
                                          ctypes.c_char_p,
                                          ctypes.c_char_p,
                                          ctypes.c_int32,
                                          ctypes.c_void_p,
                                          ctypes.POINTER(ctypes.c_uint32)]
    _item = _string_new()
    property_bits = ctypes.c_uint32(0)

    retVal = EXEMPI.xmp_get_array_item(xmp,
                              schema.encode('utf-8'),
                              name.encode('utf-8'),
                              ctypes.c_int32(index),
                              _item,
                              ctypes.byref(property_bits))

    check_error(retVal)
    item = string_cstr(_item)
    _string_free(_item)

    return item, property_bits.value
```",{},{}
