13363,IssuesEvent,2017-01-24 23:01:23+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,386473,devigned,6844498,Azure,opened,Exists should return 'true' or 'false',[],[],0,"If an exists command is available for a resource (might not be needed if one were to use show), the only two valid returns should be 'true' or 'false'.

Currently, `az group exists` returns 'true' when exists and empty when it doesn't exist. By doing this, one can't say `if [ $(az group exists -n group-that-doesnt-exit) == 'true' ]` since that would cause a `-bash: [: ==: unary operator expected` to be thrown when null is returned.",{},{}
