14434,IssuesEvent,2018-07-02 20:17:55+00:00,24043280,sshuttle/sshuttle,891419,dennybaa,8774006,sshuttle,opened,[BUG] NAT iptables return inconsistent,[],[],0,"Sshutle creates a nat table ruble `iptables -t nat -D ${SSHUTTLE_CHAIN} -d 127.0.0.1/32 -p tcp -j RETURN` this is not that actually required. What happens is that all the traffic is piped into tunnel expect traffic targeting localhost.
This _doesn't take into consideration_ that localhost is not only `127.0.0.1` address available locally!

```
Chain sshuttle-12300 (2 references)
target     prot opt source               destination         
RETURN     tcp  --  0.0.0.0/0            127.0.0.1           
```

Consistent configuration would be:

```shell
iptables -t nat -I sshuttle-12300 -m addrtype --dst-type LOCAL -j RETURN
```


PS: Also when running inside a docker container sshutle breaks all the traffic originating from the host to container exposed ports.",{},{}
