14447,IssuesEvent,2016-08-17 15:03:21+00:00,24378312,summanlp/textrank,8971160,MathiasDesch,8879217,summanlp,opened,ZeroDivisionError when one sentence text,[],[],0,"There is a `ZeroDivisionError float division by zero` raise at L76 by `pagerank_weighted.py` if I am trying to get keywords on an one sentence text: 

```python
print keywords.keywords('Product arrived labeled as Jumbo Salted Peanuts...the peanuts were actually small sized unsalted. Not sure if this was an error or if the vendor intended to represent the product as ""Jumbo"". ')
```

If I am adding just a second test sentences, it is working perfectly : 
```python
    print keywords.keywords('Product arrived labeled as Jumbo Salted Peanuts...the peanuts were actually small sized unsalted. Not sure if this was an error or if the vendor intended to represent the product as ""Jumbo"". test', ratio=1)
>>> jumbo
>>> test
```

Should not text rank work also on one sentence text ?",{},{}
