14718,IssuesEvent,2015-06-27 07:18:56+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,1581662,jdkasten,9289019,letsencrypt,closed,Null configurator,[],[],4,"For integration tests between the client and server, I'd like a fully command-line invocation of the client that uses the standalone authenticator and outputs a certificate to a file, without trying to configure a web server. It should also be able to run as non-root by binding to port 5001 instead of 443, and accept an HTTP URL for its Boulder instance.

