14720,IssuesEvent,2015-10-20 18:38:47+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,2704175,kruug,9289019,letsencrypt,opened,pem file naming can be confusing when it comes time to add them to the server config files.,[],[],0,"Currently, the two files that would need to be added to apache are:
  cert.pem
  chain.pem
  privkey.pem

and nginx are
  fullchain.pem
  privkey.pem

Looking at https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/ssl/ssl_howto.html and https://www.digicert.com/ssl-certificate-installation-apache.htm, it would appear that Apache requires `SSLCertificateFile`, `SSLCertificateKeyFile`, and `SSLCertificateChainFile`.  These would be `cert.pem`, `privkey.pem`, and `chain.pem`, respectfully.

Looking at https://www.digicert.com/ssl-certificate-installation-nginx.htm, it would appear that Nginx requires `ssl_certificate` and `ssl_certificate_key`.  These would be `fullchain.pem` and `privkey.pem`, respectfully.

I propose renaming the files to something that better matches what the documentations state for the settings.  In my mind, what makes sense would be renaming `fullchain.pem` to `certificatebundle.pem` (or certbundle.pem to keep it short) and renaming `privkey.pem` to `certificatekey.pem` (or `certkey.pem to keep it short).",{},{}
