15501,IssuesEvent,2016-02-05 05:12:46+00:00,7347535,pimusicbox/mopidy-musicbox-webclient,10268911,jcass77,11539267,pimusicbox,opened,Fullscreen not scaling correctly in landscape mode,[],[],0,"When running the web client in fullscreen mode on a mobile device, switching to landscape mode sometimes causes the page to scale incorrectly.

I've seen this on the iPhone 5s but assume the same issue will occur on other mobile devices with similar screen dimensions:

![img_1169](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10268911/12838430/caa55eca-cbd6-11e5-896a-90dcda63caeb.png)

Steps to reproduce:

1. first add Mopidy-Musibox-Webclient to the Home Screen, and then launch the client.
2. click on the search icon in the top right corner of the screen.
3. make sure that the 'Search term' input box has focus (i.e. the keyboard is displayed, ready for text entry).
4. click 'done' to make the keyboard go away.
5. rotate device to enter landscape mode.
6. incorrectly scaled screen is displayed as per the above image.

What makes this particularly annoying is that, once the scaling has gone haywire, there is no way to recover in either landscape or portrait mode. The client needs to be restarted to reset to the correct viewport.",{},{}
15514,IssuesEvent,2016-02-07 03:48:01+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,1915968,kevinclancy,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,bad model using qf_fp,[],[],0,"First off, this problem uses a 3-bit exponent and an 8-bit significand. It could probably be argued that this is an unreasonably small format, but if that is the case, then perhaps z3 should produce an error message when such a small format is used. Bumping the exponent size up to 4 fixes the problem.

I found this using z3 built from CL 993a0434b442c92e4e84103490722c5428be5ecd

I have six floating-point variables a,b,c, d, ac, and bd. They have been given the following constraints:
a /= +oo
b /= -oo
c /= +oo
d /= -oo

a <= b
c <= d

ac = a+c rounded down
bd = b+d rounded up

Furthermore, I have the assertion (not (<= ac bd))
This should not be satisfiable, since ac <= a + c <= b + d <= bd, but z3 produces a model.

[smt_test.smt2.zip](https://github.com/Z3Prover/z3/files/120556/smt_test.smt2.zip)",{},{}
15515,IssuesEvent,2016-11-04 21:24:38+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,10155819,wintersteiger,11668813,Z3Prover,closed,Updates to optimize module in ML interface,[],"[{'login': 'wintersteiger', 'id': 10155819, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10155819?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/wintersteiger', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/wintersteiger/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"The signature of get_lower and get_upper can be improved.
It currently has signature:

  (** Retrieve lower bound in current model for handle *)
  val get_lower : handle -> int -> Expr.expr

  (** Retrieve upper bound in current model for handle *)
  val get_upper : handle -> int -> Expr.expr


And the implementation is:
  let get_lower (x:handle) (idx:int) = Z3native.optimize_get_lower (gc x.opt) x.opt idx
  let get_upper (x:handle) (idx:int) = Z3native.optimize_get_upper (gc x.opt) x.opt idx

The intent with the handle is to encode opaquely the index that gets passed.
The implementation should be along the lines of:

  (** Retrieve lower bound in current model for handle *)
  val get_lower : handle -> Expr.expr

  (** Retrieve upper bound in current model for handle *)
  val get_upper : handle -> Expr.expr

with:

  let get_lower (x:handle)  = Z3native.optimize_get_lower (gc x.opt) x.opt x.h
  let get_upper (x:handle)  = Z3native.optimize_get_upper (gc x.opt) x.opt x.h

A few newer APIs can also be added:

val  from_file : optimize -> string -> unit
val  from_string : optimize -> string -> unit
val get_assertions : optimize -> Expr.expr list
val get_objectives : optimize -> Expr.expr list


",{},{}
