15566,IssuesEvent,2017-03-09 05:01:16+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,closed,Windows Installation,[],[],2,"Just wanted to clarify some things since I successfully built and installed on Windows 10 and this wasn't mentioned in the README.

Even though the build instruction says use `python scripts/mk_make.py -x --python`, this can build a package that works in python3.

The building should take place inside the Visual C++ 2015 x64 Native Build Tools Prompt`.

The `z3.exe` appears to be independent and can work anywhere, you can copy the built version wherever. The `libz3.dll` needs to be discoverable on the PATH. So you can copy both `build/z3.exe` and `build/libz3.dll` into somewhere on the PATH.

Then the `build/python/z3` directory should be copied into the site-packages directory of Python. On Windows, this isn't done automatically, instead you have to find your Windows site-packages: like `python3 -c 'import site; print(site.getsitepackages())'`, then copy the entire directory there.

Then to test if it finally all works run:

```
from z3 import *
Int('x')
```

All of this is fairly simple to automate with pip, the native build can be distributed as a binary wheel, and the result is just a storage of the z3 library along with the libz3.dll somewhere in the site-packages for Python to lookup. At the same time, the z3.exe can be put into the `Scripts` directory.",{},{}
15569,IssuesEvent,2015-09-17 09:09:34+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,1465305,wysiib,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,can not combine tuple an array sorts,[],[],0,"The code in https://gist.github.com/wysiib/fcc40987115bc8856b45 shows that tuple sorts behave differently if combined with array sorts than if combined with other sorts.

If the array sort is used instead of the integer sort, an exception is thrown:

z3exception Sort mismatch at argument #2 for function (declare-fun the_tuple (Int the_tuple) the_tuple) supplied sort is (Array Int Int).

I assume the constructed function should be (declare-fun the_tuple (Int (Array Int Int) the_tuple).

If the integer sort is used, the function is created as (declare-fun the_tuple (Int Int) the_tuple) as expected.

Tested with latest Z3 nightly build on OS X.

If you need further input let me know!",{},{}
