15837,IssuesEvent,2018-04-15 08:55:08+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,309527,afaerber,12520807,angr,opened,pygit is unmaintained and should be replaced,[],[],0,"angr has a dependency on [pygit](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pygit/0.1) in requirements.txt and setup.py. Version 0.1 is the latest version, from 2008, raising concerns about Python 3.x compatibility and Git evolution.

Pull #946 thus attempted to replace pygit with the actively maintained [pygit2](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/pygit2/0.27.0), which has a 2018 version. This causes failures in your CI due to involving a C library libgit2. @rhelmot would like to avoid that.",{},{}
