15919,IssuesEvent,2018-06-16 21:48:33+00:00,1706198,ncclient/ncclient,5408368,einarnn,12877522,ncclient,closed,confirm-commit and check fails on junos devices,[],[],4,"Invoking `commit()` with confirm timeout for Juniper devices result in executing in below xml on device
```
  <?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""UTF-8""?>
  <nc:commit xmlns:nc=""urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:netconf:base:1.0"">
  	<nc:confirmed/>
  	<nc:confirm-timeout>5</nc:confirm-timeout>
  	<nc:log>configured by junos_config</nc:log>
  </nc:commit>
```
This rpc call does not work for confirm commit as seen from device logs after exectung the rpc
```
user@junos# show | compare rollback ?
Possible completions:
  0                    2018-06-14 04:59:12 UTC by user via netconf
  1                    2018-06-14 04:59:07 UTC by user via netconf commit confirmed, rollback in 0mins
```

As per Juniper documentation here https://www.juniper.net/documentation/en_US/junos/topics/reference/tag-summary/junos-xml-protocol-commit-configuration.html the right xml tag for confirm commit and other features to work properly is `commit-configuration`.
Executing below xml with `commit-configuration` work as expected
```
  <?xml version=""1.0"" encoding=""UTF-8""?>
  <nc:commit-configuration xmlns:nc=""urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:netconf:base:1.0"">
  	<nc:confirmed/>
  	<nc:confirm-timeout>5</nc:confirm-timeout>
  	<nc:log>configured by junos_config</nc:log>
  </nc:commit-configuration>
```
Device logs
```
  user@junos# show | compare rollback ?
Possible completions:
  0                    2018-06-14 05:06:58 UTC by root via other
  1                    2018-06-14 05:01:46 UTC by user via netconf commit confirmed, rollback in 5mins
```

Also, check mode handling is not supported in current Juniper implementation of `commit` as described by Juniper documentation",{},{}
15946,IssuesEvent,2018-03-15 22:01:02+00:00,18188537,dronekit/dronekit-python,29601049,vincentwen1995,12973369,dronekit,closed,Question about creating python modules of the macro functions,[],[],0,"Hi folks.
In the examples from the tutorial, some of the macro functions, like goto(), arm_and_takeoff(), are rather useful but I found it a bit messy to put their definitions in the main script. So I was thinking about creating a separate module (say module A) to define them and import the module in the main script. 
However, as I was trying with it, since some of these functions have the dependency of the ""vehicle"" instance that is defined as ""vehicle = connect(connection_string, wait_ready=True)"" in the script, this could not be done easily. The interpreter of Python runs the imported module first before importing (rather than just copying the definitions of the functions into the main script and compiling like a C compiler), and there does not exist a similar functionality of ""extern variables"" as in C. 
Then I tried to connect to the vehicle (SITL) and define the ""vehicle"" instance directly in module A or import ""vehicle"" from the main script into module A, but neither works. Even though the scripts could be interpreted and run successfully, there was no heartbeat. I am supposing this is caused by the fact that the vehicle is connected twice respectively by the main script thread and the module thread.
So I was wondering whether there is a way to solve this problem? It would be really convenient to maintain multiple scripts if the functions are defined only in a single module.",{},{}
15972,IssuesEvent,2016-06-01 21:01:27+00:00,16469697,mps-youtube/mps-youtube,76665,flocke,12987682,mps-youtube,opened,Add --no-ytdl to default playerargs for mpv,[],[],0,"For the last few weeks I had the problem that it took a really long time (30s - 2m) to start a video playback from mpsyt. Today I realized that this has something to do with the youtube-dl support in mpv.

I assume that mpsyt passes a URL for the video to mpv which can be played directly but instead is intercepted by the youtube-dl hook in mpv which causes some kind of trouble.

Just adding `--no-ytdl` to the playerargs in the settings fixed this for me, so it should probably be there by default.",{},{}
