16416,IssuesEvent,2018-07-16 14:46:39+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,1012989,Ichimonji10,14839747,PulpQE,closed,Replace the os_is_* functions,"[{'id': 405150856, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0MDUxNTA4NTY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/labels/Issue%20Type:%20Plan', 'name': 'Issue Type: Plan', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'Ichimonji10', 'id': 1012989, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTI5ODk=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1012989?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/Ichimonji10', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Ichimonji10/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"The `os_is_*` functions set a bad precedent. There's an enormous number of combinations of system facts that one might want to discover, and having `os_is_*` functions is a recipe for an explosion in number of functions. A framework should provide more generalized tools that individual users can adapt to their needs.

A good solution would be to provide `get_os_release` or `get_redhat_release` functions that would return a dict of key/value pairs. Plugins could then write code like:

```python
def os_is_f27():
    os_release = get_os_release()
    return os_release['ID'] == 'fedora' and os_release['VERSION_ID'] == '27'
```

Or, if the implementation of that becomes problematic, something like this would still be much nicer:

```python
def os_is_f27():
    return get_os_release_id() == 'fedora' and get_os_release_version_id == '27'
```",{},{}
