16825,IssuesEvent,2017-08-01 18:31:53+00:00,32737992,napalm-automation/napalm,899716,ktbyers,16415577,napalm-automation,closed,Not understanding diffs for IOS,[],[],1,"<!--

Please, open the issue in the correct repo to help us keep things organized : )

* Here if it is a general issue or you just want to discuss something about the project.
* [napalm-base](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-base/issues) if it's a general issue not specific to a particular device, something regarding the data models or you don't know where it belongs.
* [napalm-eos](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-eos/issues) If it's an issue affecting `eos`
* [napalm-fortios](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-fortios/issues) If it's an issue affecting `fortios`
* [napalm-ios](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-ios/issues) If it's an issue affecting `ios`
* [napalm-ios-xr](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-ios-xr/issues) If it's an issue affecting `ios-xr`
* [napalm-junos](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-junos/issues) If it's an issue affecting `junos`
* [napalm-nxos](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-nxos/issues) If it's an issue affecting `nxos`
* [napalm-panos](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-panos/issues) If it's an issue affecting `panos`
* [napalm-pluribus](https://github.com/napalm-automation/napalm-pluribus/issues) If it's an issue affecting `pluribus`

-->

### Description of Issue/Question

Having a running IOS router with a config snippet like
```
crypto keyring KEYRING_FOO vrf BAR
  pre-shared-key address 1.2.3.4 key mykey1
  pre-shared-key address 5.6.7.8 key mykey2
```

in the current configuration of the device, and using a local changeset with 


```
crypto keyring KEYRING_FOO vrf BAR
  pre-shared-key address 1.2.3.4 key mykey1
  pre-shared-key address 5.6.7.8 key mykey3
```

i would expect napalm to create a diff for the third line only and when converting that to IOS commands to execute something like

```
crypto keyring KEYRING_FOO vrf BAR
  no pre-shared-key address 5.6.7.8 key mykey2
  pre-shared-key address 5.6.7.8 key mykey3
```

But this does not seem to be executed. Are there any limitations with napalm on such a config where the existing lines are nested into a subcommand and have to be removed with the appropriate ""no"" before?


Thanks for your help!
Cheers,
Heri",{},{}
