17103,IssuesEvent,2018-07-31 19:15:36+00:00,1553944,wireservice/csvkit,26463,jpmckinney,17111824,wireservice,closed,in2csv: Newline characters inside cells in other formats are preserved unescaped as new lines,"[{'id': 315350593, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMTUzNTA1OTM=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/wireservice/csvkit/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'c7def8', 'default': True}]",[],3,"This is perhaps an unusual edge case, but I've run into it today: When you're making a CSV from another format with in2csv, if a cell has a new line in it, this will be reproduced in the final CSV, with no flags or options in the CLI to escape them. 

For many CSV interpreters, this is no problem, but others, including some fairly prominent ones for R and Python, will choke on this. 

Is this something that might be worth fixing?",{},{}
