17196,IssuesEvent,2017-03-13 13:10:57+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,4831417,dean0x7d,17565521,pybind,closed,Visual Studio 2015 update 3 ICEs when using the overload_cast example.,[],[],3,"#### Issue description
I wanted to port my code that uses pybind11 on Linux to also run on Windows. However, I kept getting a C1001. I boiled it down to the use of `overload_cast`


#### Reproducible example code
I used the 64bit cmake VS generator

```cpp
#include ""pybind11/pybind11.h""

struct Pet {
    Pet(const std::string &name, int age) : name(name), age(age) { }

    void set(int age_) { age = age_; }
    void set(const std::string &name_) { name = name_; }

    std::string name;
    int age;
};


PYBIND11_PLUGIN(pytest)
{
	namespace py = pybind11;
	py::module m(
        ""pytest"", 
        ""Module description goes here."");

	py::class_<Pet>(m, ""Pet"")
		.def(""set"", py::overload_cast<int>(&Pet::set), ""Set the pet's age"")
		.def(""set"", py::overload_cast<const std::string &>(&Pet::set), ""Set the pet's name"");

    return m.ptr();
} 
```

```cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.6)
project(test_pybind11 CXX)
add_subdirectory(pybind11)
pybind11_add_module(pytest MODULE main.cpp)
```

Output from VS:

```
2> T:\test\pybind\main.cpp(21): fatal error C1001: An internal error has occurred in the compiler.
2>  (compiler file 'f:\dd\vctools\compiler\cxxfe\sl\p1\c\symbols.c', line 28467)
2>   To work around this problem, try simplifying or changing the program near the locations listed above.
2>  Please choose the Technical Support command on the Visual C++
2>   Help menu, or open the Technical Support help file for more information
2>  T:\test\pybind\main.cpp(22): note: see reference to variable template 'const pybind11::detail::overload_cast_impl<int> overload_cast<int>' being compiled
```",{},{}
