18172,IssuesEvent,2018-01-29 20:16:39+00:00,48904888,Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot,18455011,Redjumpman,23690422,Cog-Creators,opened,[V3] Custom error handling support.,[],[],0,"Please be sure to read through other issues as well to make sure what you are suggesting/reporting has not already
been suggested/reported

### Type:

- [x] Suggestion
- [ ] Bug

Adding this here for visibility based on the discussion in discord. 

Add a check for complex cogs using the special methods added in the [discord.py rewrite](https://discordpy.readthedocs.io/en/rewrite/migrating.html#cog-changes) via `__errror()`. For example, this will allow a cog like Audio to have an error message tailored to the problem. This could be integrated with the new issue templates proposed in #1275 . In addition, this could also allow cog-creators to develop their own custom error messages, such as directing people to their channel in the Cog Support server or their own GH issues. 
",{},{}
18173,IssuesEvent,2018-07-16 23:41:24+00:00,48904888,Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot,41233185,FixedThink,23690422,Cog-Creators,opened,[V3 Trivia] Users can mention `@here` and `@everyone` through a trivia session.,[],[],0,"# Command bugs

#### Command name

`[p]trivia` (found it with this one, but applies to other commands as well)

#### What cog is this command from?

Trivia (found it with this one, but applies to other commands as well)

#### What were you expecting to happen?

When a user answers a question correctly, either their username is mentioned, or their displayed name with mass mentioned escaped.

#### What actually happened?

The bot pings `@here` and `@everyone` when someone plays trivia, has one of those handles in their name, and answers a question correctly.

[Here is an image showing what happens.](https://i.imgur.com/KLsjnJk.png)

#### How can we reproduce this issue?

1.  Change your nickname to something containing `@here` or `@everyone`
2. Start a trivia session (e.g. `[p]trivia 2016`)
3. Answer a question correctly.

The line in question that causes the issue for trivia: https://github.com/Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot/blame/V3/develop/redbot/cogs/trivia/session.py#L194

And this commit (https://github.com/Cog-Creators/Red-DiscordBot/commit/b88b5a2601f56bda985729352d24842f087a8ade) shows that there might be more commands with this issue (although most are from `admin.py`.

",{},{}
