18237,IssuesEvent,2018-06-14 18:14:42+00:00,88679857,biolink/ontobio,2678599,dustine32,25489141,biolink,opened,ontol.parent_index has potential typo,[],[],0,"Noticed this method when @valearna asked me about what it does. When trying to use it, it breaks due to `b` not being defined here:
```
l.append([n] ++ g.predecessors(b))
```
When switching `b` to `n` (may be wrong here) the next error is with invalid operator `++`. Correcting to `+` then allows the result referenced in the method doc to be returned.

