18249,IssuesEvent,2017-11-09 04:47:46+00:00,34138622,jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets,192614,jasongrout,25869250,jupyter-widgets,opened,Jupyterlab output widget doesn't send appended outputs back to kernel,[],[],0,"The output widget should send the appended outputs back to the kernel, but doesn't. It should sync the outputs on both the `add` and `clear` methods: https://github.com/jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets/blob/master/packages/jupyterlab-manager/src/output.ts#L78

The classic notebook output widget does do this:

* https://github.com/jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets/blob/master/widgetsnbextension/src/widget_output.js#L43
* https://github.com/jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets/blob/master/widgetsnbextension/src/widget_output.js#L48

The output widget should also listen to syncs from the outputs in the kernel, like the classic notebook output widget does: https://github.com/jupyter-widgets/ipywidgets/blob/master/widgetsnbextension/src/widget_output.js#L50",{},{}
