18285,IssuesEvent,2018-08-01 01:53:14+00:00,35531022,opendatacube/datacube-core,1428024,Kirill888,26125288,opendatacube,opened,Handling of NaN values during indexing,[],[],0,"On NCI install, `NaN` values get stored as strings in the DB.

Some scenes in the `ls8_level1_scene` have `NaN` values in the `gqa` subtree, they appear correctly in the yaml document, but appear as strings in the database:

- uuid: `d30ebe7e-237f-4783-af03-90ef91bc081d`
- file: `/g/data/v10/reprocess/ls8/level1/2018/05/LS8_OLITIRS_OTH_P41_GALPGS01-032_088_078_20180504/ga-metadata.yaml`

File on disk has proper `.nan` and loads in python with `yaml.safe_load` giving `NaN`:

```yaml
id: d30ebe7e-237f-4783-af03-90ef91bc081d
ga_label: LS8_OLITIRS_OTH_P41_GALPGS01-032_088_078_20180504
product_type: level1
product_level: L1GT
creation_dt: 2018-07-09 11:08:01
...
gqa:
    error_message: No reference or backup reference imagery available.
    final_gcp_count: 0
    ref_date: null
    ref_source: null
    ref_source_path: null
    residual:
        abs:
            x: .nan
            xy: .nan
            y: .nan
        abs_iterative_mean:
            x: .nan
            xy: .nan
            y: .nan
        cep90: .nan
``` 

However data stored in DB has a 3 char string `""NaN""`

```json
{
  ""id"": ""d30ebe7e-237f-4783-af03-90ef91bc081d"",
  ""gqa"": {
    ""ref_date"": null,
    ""residual"": {
      ""abs"": {
        ""x"": ""NaN"",
        ""y"": ""NaN"",
        ""xy"": ""NaN""
      },
      ""abs_iterative_mean"": {
        ""x"": ""NaN"",
        ""y"": ""NaN"",
        ""xy"": ""NaN""
      }
...
  }
...
}
```

This was observed while testing sync tool by @santoshamohan, sync tool *correctly* reports inconsistency between lineage data and DB version.",{},{}
