18300,IssuesEvent,2018-01-28 04:44:35+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,609896,njsmith,26335827,python-trio,closed,Investigate yapf 0.18.0 release,[],[],2,"For some reason the new yapf 0.18.0 wants to reformat everything: https://travis-ci.org/python-trio/trio/jobs/279922409

I don't see [anything in the CHANGELOG about this](https://github.com/google/yapf/blob/master/CHANGELOG); there's a suspicious comment in the changelog for 0.17, but 0.17 is what we've been using; the change is from the 0.18 release. Maybe the CHANGELOG has that change filed in the wrong place.

We need to either re-run yapf, or possibly change our config file to keep the old formatting. (I think I might prefer the old version, and I think there might be a flag to control this and the bug they fixed is that the flag was being accidentally forced to a particular value instead of respecting the config file.)",{},{}
18321,IssuesEvent,2018-06-21 17:08:34+00:00,71482397,Parsl/parsl,181489,yadudoc,26490185,Parsl,closed,Parsl version conflict with libsubmit 0.4.1,"[{'id': 465598054, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NjU1OTgwNTQ=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsl/parsl/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'yadudoc', 'id': 181489, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjE4MTQ4OQ==', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/181489?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/yadudoc', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yadudoc/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"Libsubmit 0.4.1 makes several changes to the provider interfaces that will not work with Parsl v0.5.1 and earlier. All Parsl versions released till now specify libsubmit>=XX>YY>ZZ as a requirement, meaning if the user explicitly updates libsubmit, they could end with incompatible versions. This means that until the next release is made, users making fresh parsl installs will be faced with incompatible parsl and libsubmit versions. 

I'm working on a quick 0.5.2 point release as a stop gap.",{},{}
