18413,IssuesEvent,2018-04-24 12:35:21+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,19791853,octopus2705,28732122,localstack,opened,S3 pre-signed url with query parameters,[],[],0,"Hi,
I am uploading a file to S3 using pre-signed url via HTTP PUT request. It has some query parameters in the pre-signed url as follows-

http://s3-bucket.localhost:4572/folder/file.txt?x-amz-meta-filename=file.txt&x-amz-meta-fileSource=source

The file is upload to S3 successfully but notification to lambda is not triggered. Though if I put the same file via aws cli and put-object command, the lambda is invoked.

Out of curiosity I was looking at the code of https://github.com/localstack/localstack/blob/master/localstack/services/s3/s3_listener.py and found a flag 'should_send_notifications' which seems to prevent notifications to lambda if url contains query parameters.

Can you please advise on why s3 notification is not triggered via pre-signed url file upload to s3?

Thanks



",{},{}
18439,IssuesEvent,2018-05-04 11:00:30+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,1621864,Fernerkundung,29057552,sentinelsat,closed,Remove list of valid producttypes from CLI,"[{'id': 214922608, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/sentinelsat/sentinelsat/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': True}]",[],5,"Currently the sentinelsat CLI has a list of valid values for the option `--producttype` implemented with

`click.Choice(['SLC', 'GRD', 'OCN', 'RAW', 'S2MSI1C', 'S2MSI2Ap'])`

This list is only complete for the Copernicus Open Access Hub but is missing the all available producttypes for the S3 PreOps-Hub.

With the upcoming merge of S3 into the regular hub as well as new missions like S5P I propose to remove the click choice and let users type any product type they like.

The list of products is a nice guide but makes the option unuseable for any DHuS instance with product types other than the ones defined in the OpenHub.

To help users what they can enter in the field I'd say we can include a list of known product types into the documentation or link to an official list (if it exists).

edit:

This would entail a small refactoring in `cli.py` regarding the `producttype` option and is a good first issue / suitable for beginners.",{},{}
